6. ARRAYS
---------
6.1 Creating Arrays
- Arrays store ordered collections of values.
- Can hold different types (numbers, strings, objects, etc.).
Examples:
let numbers = [1, 2, 3];
let fruits = ["apple", "banana"];
let mixed = [1, "Ajay", true];
let empty = [];

6.2 Accessing, Updating, Deleting
let fruits = ["apple", "banana", "cherry"];
console.log(fruits[0]);      // "apple" (index starts at 0)
fruits[1] = "mango";         // update index 1
delete fruits[2];            // removes value but leaves empty slot
// Good Practice: Use array methods (splice) instead of delete for clean removal.

6.3 Array Methods
-----------------
Mutating (changes original array):
- push(): add element at end
- pop(): remove last element
- shift(): remove first element
- unshift(): add element at start
- splice(start, deleteCount, ...items): remove/replace/add elements
- sort(): sorts (alphabetical for strings, ASCII order for numbers)
- reverse(): reverses the array

Non-mutating (returns new array, does not change original):
- slice(start, end): returns subarray
- concat(): joins arrays
- join(separator): joins into string
- includes(value): check if exists
- indexOf(value): index of first occurrence
- find(fn): first element matching condition
- filter(fn): all elements matching condition
- map(fn): transform each element, return new array
- reduce(fn, initial): reduce to single value
- forEach(fn): iterate over array (no return)

Examples:
let arr = [1, 2, 3, 4];
console.log(arr.slice(1, 3));     // [2,3]
console.log(arr.concat([5, 6]));  // [1,2,3,4,5,6]
console.log(arr.join("-"));       // "1-2-3-4"
console.log(arr.includes(3));     // true
console.log(arr.indexOf(2));      // 1
console.log(arr.find(x => x > 2));    // 3
console.log(arr.filter(x => x % 2 === 0)); // [2,4]
console.log(arr.map(x => x * 2));  // [2,4,6,8]
console.log(arr.reduce((sum, x) => sum + x, 0)); // 10
arr.forEach(x => console.log(x));  // logs 1,2,3,4

6.4 Array Destructuring
let [a, b] = [10, 20];
console.log(a); // 10
console.log(b); // 20

let [first, , third] = [1, 2, 3];
console.log(first, third); // 1 3

6.5 Nested / Multidimensional Arrays
let matrix = [
  [1, 2, 3],
  [4, 5, 6],
  [7, 8, 9]
];
console.log(matrix[1][2]); // 6
